      StoryChapter(
        heading: 'Ramalan yang Tergenapi',
        headingEn: 'The Prophecy Fulfilled',
        body:
            '''Meski kemenangannya gemilang, ramalan lama masih menanti penggenapannya. Perseus pergi ke Larissa untuk mengikuti pertandingan atletik. Saat melempar cakram (diskus), lemparannya melenceng karena angin atau kehendak takdir dan mengenai seorang penonton tua hingga tewas. Penonton itu tak lain adalah Akrisios, kakeknya sendiri, yang melarikan diri dari Argos justru karena takut akan ramalan itu. Demikianlah nubuat tergenapi bukan lewat kebencian, melainkan lewat kecelakaan yang tak terelakkan. Karena malu mewarisi takhta orang yang tak sengaja dibunuhnya, Perseus menukar kerajaan Argos dengan Tiryns. Ia lalu mendirikan kota besar Mikene. Dari garis keturunan Perseus dan Andromeda kelak lahir banyak pahlawan, termasuk Herakles sang perkasa, sehingga wiracarita ini menjadi akar bagi silsilah kepahlawanan Yunani.''',
        bodyEn:
            '''Though his triumph was glorious, the old prophecy still awaited its fulfillment. Perseus travelled to Larissa to compete in athletic games. As he threw the discus, his cast went astray — by the wind or by fate\'s design — and struck an old spectator, killing him. That spectator was none other than Acrisius, his own grandfather, who had fled Argos precisely for fear of the prophecy. Thus the oracle was fulfilled not through hatred but through an unavoidable accident. Ashamed to inherit the throne of a man he had unwittingly killed, Perseus exchanged the kingdom of Argos for Tiryns. He then founded the great city of Mycenae. From the line of Perseus and Andromeda many heroes would later descend, including the mighty Heracles, making this saga the root of the Greek heroic genealogy.''',
