    impact:
        '''Kemenangan Perseus menegaskan pola pahlawan Yunani yang menaklukkan monster berkat bantuan dewa dan akal budi, bukan sekadar kekuatan. Ia mendirikan Mikene, pusat kekuasaan legendaris, dan menurunkan garis keturunan yang berpuncak pada Herakles. Kepala Medusa menjadi lambang aigis Athena, senjata pelindung sekaligus penebar teror. Ramalan yang tergenapi menegaskan keyakinan Yunani bahwa takdir tak dapat dielakkan.''',
    impactEn:
        '''Perseus\'s triumph established the pattern of the Greek hero who conquers monsters through divine aid and cunning rather than raw strength alone. He founded Mycenae, a legendary seat of power, and fathered the line that culminated in Heracles. Medusa\'s head became the emblem of Athena\'s aegis, a weapon of protection and terror alike. The fulfilled prophecy reaffirmed the Greek conviction that fate cannot be escaped.''',
    meaning:
        '''Kisah Perseus melambangkan kemenangan atas ketakutan yang tak dapat ditatap langsung: Medusa hanya bisa dikalahkan lewat pantulan, yakni lewat kebijaksanaan dan jarak, bukan konfrontasi buta. Perisai cermin Athena menyiratkan bahwa nalar mengalahkan teror. Sepanjang sejarah, kepala Medusa menjadi jimat penangkal kejahatan (apotropaik), sementara ramalan yang tergenapi mengajarkan bahwa upaya melawan takdir justru sering mewujudkannya.''',
    meaningEn:
        '''The tale of Perseus symbolizes the conquest of a terror that cannot be faced directly: Medusa can only be defeated through reflection — through wisdom and distance rather than blind confrontation. Athena\'s mirrored shield implies that reason overcomes terror. Through the ages, Medusa\'s head became a protective, evil-averting (apotropaic) charm, while the fulfilled prophecy teaches that efforts to escape fate often bring it to pass.''',
